    <section id="faq" data-section-key="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <details><summary>What does it cost?</summary><p>Ongoing care starts at €149/month as an entry price (for example 1 server and up to 5 workstations). One-off jobs and projects get a one-page fixed-price quote after the free initial consultation. Both without counting hours, larger environments at a fixed price after a quick check.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Am I locked into a contract?</summary><p>No. Projects are one-off fixed-price engagements, monthly care can be cancelled. I'd rather convince through work than through contract terms.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What happens in an outage or data loss?</summary><p>For acute issues you reach me directly by phone and I deal with it as a priority. Maintenance clients have a fixed response time: within 12 hours on business days. As a precaution, tested backups are in place: we verify restores <em>before</em> the emergency and document how they work.</p></details>
        <details><summary>You work alone, what happens if you're unavailable?</summary><p>Fair question. I document everything so that someone else can take over in an emergency, instead of hoarding knowledge in my head. On top of that come the tested, off-site backups and a reachable emergency number. So your operation doesn't depend on my presence, but on a documented, recoverable setup.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How do you handle data protection and GDPR?</summary><p>A data processing agreement (DPA) is part of every engagement. Data stays on systems in Germany, backups are encrypted, access rights are clearly defined. I work aligned with the German BSI baseline-protection methodology, which is a way of working, not a certification.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you see our data when maintaining our systems?</summary><p>To maintain your IT I need access to systems, not to your content. I work on configuration, structure and scripts. Your actual data (database contents, documents, emails) stays on your systems. If a specific task genuinely requires real data, it only happens by arrangement, documented, and under the data processing agreement.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Will I understand what's being done?</summary><p>Yes, that's part of the job. No jargon, everything documented in writing and explained so you can pass it on to your team.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you use AI for development?</summary><p>Yes, as a tool for routine work. Architecture, security, review and responsibility stay with me. Your confidential content is not simply fed into public AI services.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

